Paper: hep-th/9911067

Date: 1999-11-10

Title: M Theory and Cosmology

Authors: Tom Banks

Comments: JHEP LaTeX, 86 pages, 3 eps figures

This is a series of lectures on M Theory for cosmologists. After summarizingsome of the main properties of M Theory and its dualities I show how it can beused to address various fundamental and phenomenological issues in cosmology.